Type: Package
Package: autoLIMR
Title: Automated Translation of Network Data into Declaration Files
    Compatible with 'LIM' and 'limSolve'
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Gemma", "Gerber", email = "gemmagerber@live.com", role =
    c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-8722-3113")),
    person("Ben", "Brooker", role = "ctb"))
Maintainer: Gemma Gerber <gemmagerber@live.com>
Description: Using linear inverse modelling (LIM) via R packages 'LIM' and
    'limSolve' are a great way to calculate multiple plausible network
    solutions. These packages require network data to be coded into "LIM
    Declaration Files", which can be be tedious and difficult to manually
    code. 'autoLIMR' provides an automated translation from network data (in
    .xlsx format) to LIM declaration files compatible with 'LIM' and
    'limSolve'. 'autoLIMR' provides the option to translate multiple network
    datasets into multiple LIM Declaration Files at once.
